<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-05-20T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-05-20T14:00:00-05:00" n="577" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00 Revolutions/119: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-20T13:00:00-06:00">May 20, 1931—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:55 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>106. Agree with telegram from Comsperon to Chief of Naval Operations one
                            warship on north coast, Honduras, amply covers present situation and
                            advisable for reasons of policy not send another now unless necessary
                            relieve <hi rend="italic">Marblehead.</hi></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>